      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Pitfalls"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Relying solely on the keyword blocklist:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " trivially bypassed with synonyms, acronyms, or non-English phrasing."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Treating the CLIP safety checker as foolproof:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " its fixed concept embeddings have no coverage over concepts not in its original training list."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Aggressive thresholds causing false positives:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " medical, artistic, and historical content occupies CLIP regions near NSFW concepts. Always evaluate on a domain-representative false-positive set."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Applying concept erasure too broadly:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " ESD training can degrade generation quality for related benign concepts (concept bleed). Target only the specific representations that need removal."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "No logging or audit trail:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " safety systems require ongoing monitoring. Log blocked prompts (without storing PII) to measure filter drift as user behaviour evolves."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Core principles:",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "bold"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " Safety filters in text-to-image systems form a multi-layer stack: prompt blocklists and embedding filters prevent unsafe generation before it starts; concept erasure removes capabilities at the weight level so adversarial prompts cannot recover them; Safe Latent Diffusion redirects generation at inference time without retraining; output classifiers provide a final backstop. No single layer is sufficient. The default SD CLIP safety checker works by measuring cosine similarity between the decoded image and fixed unsafe concept embeddings — it can produce false positives on medical and artistic content and is bypassable via style or palette tricks. For production deployments, combine all layers, tune thresholds on domain-representative data, and maintain an audit log to detect drift."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
